# Task 1: Research & Foundation Setup

## Primary Objective
Create a working proof-of-concept integrating WebLLM with SwarmDesk's agent dialogue system.

## Key Focus Areas
- Analyze current agent response system in [swarmdesk.js](mdc:swarmdesk.js) `generateAgentResponse()`
- Integrate WebLLM basic functionality with single agent (recommend Git Assistant)
- Test browser compatibility (WebGPU support)
- Benchmark model loading times and performance

## Core Files to Study
- [swarmdesk.js](mdc:swarmdesk.js) - Agent dialogue system around lines 2090-2129
- [index.html](mdc:index.html) - Current UI structure
- [swarmdesk-dashboard-hooks.js](mdc:swarmdesk-dashboard-hooks.js) - Dashboard integration patterns

## Implementation Strategy
1. Add WebLLM dependency: `npm install @mlc-ai/web-llm`
2. Create basic WebLLM engine initialization
3. Replace `generateAgentResponse()` for one agent type
4. Test with small model (e.g., "RedPajama-INCITE-Chat-3B-v1-q4f32_1")
5. Document browser requirements and performance baseline

## Expected Deliverables
- Working WebLLM integration with Git Assistant
- Browser compatibility documentation
- Performance benchmarks
- Foundation code for Task 2 expansion
